    <name>Sevoflurane</name>
    <description>Sevoflurane is a halogenated inhalational anesthetic used for induction and maintenance of general anesthesia.</description>
    <mechanism-of-action>Sevoflurane enhances inhibitory neurotransmission via GABA-A and glycine receptors while inhibiting excitatory NMDA receptors.</mechanism-of-action>
    <pharmacodynamics>Sevoflurane provides smooth induction with minimal airway irritation.</pharmacodynamics>
